criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age ≥18 and ≤ 80 years;

          -  Biopsy proven clinically localized prostate cancer;

          -  Informed consent obtained and signed;

          -  Understanding of, and willingness to comply with, the study procedures.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Pre-operative incontinence;

          -  Salvage prostatectomy (defined as a prostatectomy prescribed after the failure of a
             different primary treatment);

          -  Surgical posterior plane at the peri - rectal fat, without preserving an edge of the
             Denonvilliers;

          -  History of psychiatric or addictive disorder or other medical condition that, in the
             opinion of the investigator, would preclude the patient from meeting the trial
             requirements;
